com.serena.dmclient.api
Interface DimensionsLcObject

All Superinterfaces:
DimensionsArObject, DimensionsObject
All Known Subinterfaces:
Baseline, ItemRevision, Part, Project, Request
public interface DimensionsLcObject
extends DimensionsArObject

Represents a Dimensions object that follows a lifecycle and has action history and user-defined attributes.

A note about sensitive attributes

When calling actionTo(String, int[]), if any of the attributes in question have been marked as sensitive, authorization point information will be required. If it has not been supplied, an exception will be thrown. This method will then only be satisfied if the correct authorization point information has been supplied in the system attribute AUTHORIZATION_POINT_INFO. The code below is an example of how to cope with this situation for a single request:

        Request cd = (Request) cdocs.get(i);
        int sensitiveAttributeNumber = ...
        cd.setAttribute(sensitiveAttributeNumber, "a new value");
        boolean authReqd, authFailed, succeeded = false;
        int attempts = 0;
        while(!succeeded & attempts < 3) { //<- you shouldn't actually need to impose this check, the server will only allow 3 attempts
                try {
                        cd.actionTo("ACCEPTED", new int[]{sensitiveAttrNum});
                        succeeded = true;
                } catch (AuthorizationRequiredException are) {
                        authReqd = true;
                } catch (AuthorizationFailedException afe) {
                        authFailed = true;
                } finally {
                        if (authReqd) {
                                authReqd = false;
                                cd.setAttribute(SystemAttributes.AUTHORIZATION_POINT_INFO, "incorrect_password");//<- this could come from a GUI
                        } else if (authFailed) {
                                authFailed = false;
                                cd.setAttribute(SystemAttributes.AUTHORIZATION_POINT_INFO, "correct_password");//<- this could come from a GUI
                        }
                }
                attempts ++;
        }

For multiple objects, it is advisable to set the AUTHORIZATION_POINT_INFO attribute on all of them before calling actionTo(). This will allow a bulk calling of actionTo() to take place without an exception being thrown for each one.

The server allows 3 unsuccessful attempts at updating a sensitive attribute, after which it will fail silently.
